Text.Value: The githyanki asked me to teach her some combat techniques - naturally, I was pleased to be consulted.
You're a murderer, Minthara. I can't let you walk away.
All right. I'm with you.
Someone has betrayed our presence here. A spy.
I dealt with her.
You - you killed Minsc?
You - you killed Isobel?
Let's do it while they're awake. It'll be more enjoyable. Please.
We can talk them around. They listen to me.
Yes. Menzoberranzan rules. If we're found, we die.
When we met, I was beholden to a cult dedicated to a false god that controlled me through a parasite in my brain.
Of course I did. Anyone who threatens me either kills me, or dies.
Not the first. I killed my sister in her crib to secure my inheritance.
This latest conspiracy is rather ordinary in comparison. As is the solution.
Naturally, she didn't stand a chance. I dealt with her.
Do you have any proof of this?
With one exception. You.
The creature confessed, of course. Their childish bravado didn't last long. They told me everything.
As are you. Consider yourself lucky that I trust you, or you would not be alive to doubt me.
Children should not play at such dangerous games, if they fear getting hurt. This one made some dangerous friends.
I have heard them whisper, I have seen the way they look at me. They begin to see you in the same light.
No. If the blood-witch were here, I'd be able to smell her.
Ravengard asked to speak with me alone, and the moment my back was turned, he tried to kill me.
It was the girl, Yenna. I have dealt with the problem.
You - you killed Wyll?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Minthara steps aside. Behind her, we see a heap on the floor, human sized, covered with a dark, bloody cloth. No part of the body is visible, but a pool of blood is just visible beneath it.

Text.Value: You're such a disappointment.
Will you watch when the others kill me? Will you hold my head back while they cut my throat? Whisper goodbyes as I gasp and bleed?

EditorData.NodeContext: with a smile - knows her plan is about to be set in motion

Text.Value: The cult.
Surviving what comes next.
You killed a child?
But the moment we were alone, she spouted some drivel about my integrity and loyalty.
That fawning cleric Isobel asked to speak with me alone. Told me her goddess had asked her to extinguish me.
Let's butcher them all - I've been waiting for an excuse.
My life is in danger. As I knew it would be the moment I joined you.
You - you killed Gale?
That is the correct course. I was prepared to convince you - I am glad I do not have to.
Grim work. But it has to be done.
Why should I trust you on this? You're a murderer!
First, we must dispose of the body. What comes next will be... simpler if we don't arouse suspicions.
Wyll asked to speak with me alone, and the moment my back was turned, he tried to kill me.
Conspirators? Assassins? Listen to yourself, Minthara.
He tried to kill me.
I will not apologise for defending myself.
Good. Nobody saw you arrive - that will be to our advantage.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player follows Minthara to a secluded area.

Text.Value: Pathetic. You don't negotiate with people who wish you dead. You kill them.
The vampire asked to speak to me alone. Accused me of being a threat to your wellbeing, if you can believe it.
You - you killed Jaheira?
Minsc asked to speak to me alone - I expected his usual righteous drivel. Annoying, but harmless.
You - you killed Karlach?
I overpowered her, of course. A thief I can tolerate, but under duress she admitted to being a spy.
They plan to attack our camp. Tonight.
We need to kill them all.
I may have been too late. She already reported to her superiors.
Who do you think sent them?
The aasimar asked for a word in private. I find her sanctimony irritating, but I agreed to speak with her.
You - you killed Astarion?
Idiot. Think with your brain, not your groin for once.
I welcome you into my camp, and this is how you repay me?
Are we playing hide and seek?
I don't want to be an accessory to child murder.
We must not rest tonight. We must lie in wait for them.
You - you killed Aylin?
Our relationship disturbs them. It is not only me they conspire to assassinate. They will kill us both.
Good work. Our camp is in safe hands with you.
I only kill when it is necessary. This was necessary.
She was confused. Said the gods had a plan for her, and that I was a threat to it.
And then she tried to kill me.
But this time was different. He tried to kill me.
And then she tried to kill me.
You're covered in gore. More so than usual.
How do you know they were a spy?
The cult plan to attack our camp. Tonight.
I think Orin is behind this - she may have infiltrated our camp.
You made this mess. You're on your own.
This threat has been with us since Moonrise.
Whatever her crimes, I can't abide the murder of a child in our camp.
I don't understand. Why would anyone try to kill you now?
My proof lies beneath that blanket.
Gale asked to speak with me alone, and the moment my back was turned, he tried to kill me.
Our advantage for what?
Definitely dismemberment.
You - you killed Shadowheart?
You - you killed Ravengard?
Jaheira took me to one side - told me the whole party are against me. That she was the only one bold enough to do what needed to be done.
Opportunism. My guard was down. It was the first time - it will be the last.
All I had to do was twist my knife.
You killed Yenna?
Now we are both in danger.
Tempting tempting tempting. But not yet. Not yet.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Orin-as-Minthara smiles at the player, seductively

Text.Value: You really are wonderful.
I'm sorry, Minthara. I thought you would be safe here.
You are not to blame. It is easy for one who has lived a coddled life to mistake my caution for paranoia.
I knew you couldn't wait to get me alone again.
You. This way. Quickly. Eyes down.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: As the party enters camp, they are intercepted by a bloodied and bruised Minthara. She indicates for them to follow her.
Minthara steps aside. Behind her, we see a heap on the floor, human sized, covered with a dark, bloody cloth. No part of the body is visible, but a pool of blood is just visible beneath it.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [DG] Laezel (Orin) transforms into her true form.

Text.Value: Naturally, he didn't stand a chance. I dealt with him.
I caught the girl, Yenna, rifling through my belongings. When I confronted her, she pulled a knife on me.
You - you killed Lae'zel?
Observant as ever.
You could stick me through the heart. Stick her through the heart. Cut us to bits.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player/party draw their weapon. Minthara smiles
EditorData.NodeContext: with a smile - knows her plan is about to be set in motion

Text.Value: The others have despised my presence here since I joined you.
That brute Karlach asked to speak to me alone. Told me I was no better than the devils who once imprisoned her.
First, we must dispose of their little spy. Burial or dismemberment. Either will suffice.
Shadowheart came to me, flashing those puppy-dog eyes. Asked for my counsel, in private.
When the body is hidden, we wait until the dead of night, and kill the others as they sleep.

Synopsis:
The first longrest in Undercity, Orin will abduct one of the players companion. (Laezel, Halsin, Gale or Minthara). Based on the players approval rating with them. (Friend, Good Friend and Romance) Highest approval will be the highest priority.

She will appear in camp impersonating her abducted victim and toy with the players. Shortly after, she grows tire of the game and reveals herself. And gives her ultimatum - Kill Gortash and retrieve his Netherstone - and bring it to her at her Bhaal Temple. Or the abducted companion dies. She will then teleport away.
